# Keep the build context small. The Dockerfile only needs:
#   wizard/package.json wizard/package-lock.json wizard/<source>
#   deploys/byo/templates/
#
# Build context is the secret-claw/ repo root (set in docker-compose.yml).
# Anything else under the repo root that isn't wizard/ or
# deploys/byo/templates/ is irrelevant to the image.

# Everything by default
*

# Then allow back the bits we actually need:
!wizard/
!deploys/

# But not the heavy / generated / sensitive subtrees
wizard/node_modules
wizard/.next
wizard/out
wizard/.env
wizard/.env.local
wizard/.env.*.local
wizard/tests
wizard/prototypes
wizard/Dockerfile
wizard/docker-compose.yml
wizard/dev.log
wizard/*.log

# We only need the templates from deploys/byo/, not the scripts or examples
deploys/byo/scripts
deploys/byo/example-config
deploys/byo/README.md
deploys/secret
